==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Darlingtonia
<hw>Dar`ling*to"ni*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.
Named after Dr. William <etsep>Darlington</etsep>, a botanist of West
Chester, Penn.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of California
pitcher plants consisting of a single species. The long tubular leaves
are hooded at the top, and frequently contain many insects drowned in
the secretion of the leaves.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Darmera</ent>⟦br⟧
